===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A gentle [[bend]], such as in a road.
#: ''You should slow down when approaching a '''curve'''.''
# A simple figure containing no [[straight]] portions and no [[angle]]s; a [[curved]] [[line]].
#: ''She scribbled a '''curve''' on the paper.''
# A grading system based on the scale of performance of a group used to [[normalize]] a right-[[skewed]] grade distribution (with more lower scores) into a [[bell curve]], so that more can receive higher grades, regardless of their actual knowledge of the subject.
#: ''The teacher was nice and graded the test on a '''curve'''''
# {{context|analytic geometry|lang=en}} A [[continuous map]] from a one-[[dimensional]] [[space]] to a multidimensional space.
# {{context|geometry|lang=en}} A one-dimensional figure of [[non-zero]] length; the [[graph]] of a continuous map from a one-dimensional space.
# {{context|algebraic geometry|lang=en}} An [[algebraic curve]]; a [[polynomial]] [[relation]] of the planar coordinates.
# {{context|topology|lang=en}} A one-dimensional [[continuum]].
# {{context|informal|usually in plural|lang=en}} The attractive shape of a woman's body.

